For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all enzymes in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot annotated to catalyze reactions involving that lipid.
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 16
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?uniprot
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId

natural_language_question: What are the Homo sapiens genes associated with cancer and their orthologs expressed in the Rattus norvegicus brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?humanGeneName ?ratGeneName ?ratAnatomicEntityLabel
WHERE {
  # Find human proteins associated with cancer
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/> {
    ?humanProtein a up:Protein ;
      up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Homo sapiens
      up:encodedBy ?humanGene .
    ?humanGene rdfs:label ?humanGeneName .
    ?humanProtein up:annotation ?diseaseAnnotation .
    ?diseaseAnnotation a up:Disease_Annotation .
    ?diseaseAnnotation rdfs:comment ?diseaseName .
    FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?diseaseName), "cancer")) # Filter for cancer-related diseases
  }

  # Find orthologs of the human proteins in Rattus norvegicus using OMA Browser
  SERVICE <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    ?cluster a orth:ParalogsCluster .
    ?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?humanNode , ?ratNode .
    ?humanNode orth:hasHomologousMember* ?humanOrthoProtein .
    ?ratNode orth:hasHomologousMember* ?ratOrthoProtein .
    ?humanOrthoProtein lscr:xrefUniprot ?humanProtein .
    ?ratOrthoProtein lscr:xrefUniprot ?ratProtein .
    ?ratOrthoProtein orth:organism/<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162> taxon:10116 . # Rattus norvegicus
  }

  # Find the rat gene associated with the orthologous protein
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/> {
    ?ratProtein a up:Protein ;
      up:encodedBy ?ratGene .
    ?ratGene rdfs:label ?ratGeneName .
  }

  # Find where the rat gene is expressed in Bgee, specifically in the brain
  SERVICE <https://www.bgee.org/sparql/> {
    ?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicEntity .
    ?gene lscr:xrefEnsemblGene ?ratGene . # Link to Ensembl gene ID
    ?anatomicEntity rdfs:label ?ratAnatomicEntityLabel .
    FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?ratAnatomicEntityLabel), "brain")) # Filter for expression in brain
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve human enzymes that metabolize sphingolipids and are annotated in ChEMBL
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX cco: <http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/terms/chembl#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?proteinName ?chemblMolecule ?chemblMoleculeLabel
WHERE {
  # Find human proteins
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 .

  # Find enzymes
  ?protein up:annotation ?annotation .
  ?annotation a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .

  # Connect to Rhea to find reactions involving sphingolipids
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/Reaction> .
    ?reaction <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/side> ?reactionSide .
    ?reactionSide <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/contains> ?participant .
    ?participant <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/compound> ?compound .
    ?compound <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/chebi> ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:64583 .  # Sphingolipids in ChEBI
  }

  # Link UniProt proteins to Rhea reactions
  ?annotation up:catalyticActivity ?catalyticActivity .
  ?catalyticActivity up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .
  ?protein up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?proteinName .

  # Find drugs in ChEMBL that interact with the UniProt Proteins
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql/endpoint/idsm> {
    ?activity a cco:Activity ;
      cco:hasMolecule ?chemblMolecule ;
      cco:hasAssay ?assay .
    ?chemblMolecule rdfs:label ?chemblMoleculeLabel .
    ?assay cco:hasTarget ?target .
    ?target cco:hasTargetComponent/cco:targetCmptXref ?protein .
    ?protein a cco:UniprotRef .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Connect patents cited in UniProtKB with those in the patent database at EPO via publication number, whose grant date is more than twenty years in the past.
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX patent: <http://data.epo.org/linked-data/def/patent/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

SELECT ?citation ?patent ?application ?applicationNo ?grantDate
WHERE
{
  # Find patent citations in UniProtKB
  ?citation a up:Patent_Citation ;
    skos:exactMatch ?patent .
  FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?patent), 'EP'))
  BIND(SUBSTR(STR(?patent), 35) AS ?applicationNo)

  # Query the EPO database for patent information
  SERVICE <https://data.epo.org/linked-data/query>{
    ?application patent:publicationNumber ?applicationNo ;
                 patent:grantDate ?grantDate .
    
    # Filter for patents granted more than 20 years ago
    FILTER (?grantDate < (NOW() - xsd:duration("P20Y")))
  }
}

# This query federates with UniProt to retrieve human proteins and Rhea to retrieve reactions.

# Therefore, this query focuses on finding similar proteins within UniProt,

PREFIX uniprotkb: <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT 
    ?similar ?identity
WHERE
{
    # Bind the UniProtKB entry of interest
    BIND (uniprotkb:P05067 AS ?protein)
    
    # Find UniRef clusters containing the protein
    ?cluster up:member ?member ;
             up:member/up:sequenceFor ?protein;

    ?member up:sequenceFor ?similar .
    
    # Exclude the original protein from the results
    FILTER(!sameTerm(?similar, ?protein))
} 
ORDER BY DESC(?identity)

# This query aims to retrieve information about the human metabolome by querying UniProt and potentially other relevant databases.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .

    ?recName up:fullName ?proteinName .

natural_language_question: Retrieve parent reactions (and their catalyzing enzymes) for a metabolite that is not directly involved in a reaction (ex: CHEBI:83137).
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?ecNumber
  (count(?protein) as ?proteinCount)
  ?reaction
  ?equation
WHERE {
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  CHEBI:83137 rdfs:subClassOf+ ?chebi.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
    {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber} .
  }
} 
GROUP BY ?chebi ?ecNumber ?reaction ?equation
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?parentReaction ?parentEquation ?enzyme ?protein
WHERE {
  # Bind the ChEBI ID of interest
  BIND (CHEBI:83137 AS ?chebi)

  # Find reactions where the metabolite is NOT directly involved
  FILTER NOT EXISTS {
    ?reaction rh:side ?side .
    ?side rh:contains ?participant .
    ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  }

  # Find parent reactions of those reactions
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf ?parentReaction .
  ?parentReaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?parentReaction rh:equation ?parentEquation .

  # OPTIONAL: Find enzymes catalyzing the parent reactions using UniProt
  OPTIONAL {
    ?parentReaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
    SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
      ?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber .
      ?protein a up:Protein .
      ?protein rdfs:seeAlso ?enzyme . # Assuming rdfs:seeAlso links to enzyme resources
    }
  }
}

natural_language_question: Use IDSM Sachem to find ChEBIs with a a Cholestane skeleton (in SMILES). Then match returned ChEBIs to Rhea undirected reactions.
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?chebi ?chebiName ?reaction ?equation
WHERE {
  # Find ChEBIs with a Cholestane skeleton using the IDSM Sachem service.
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql> {
    SELECT ?chebi WHERE {
      ?chebi a <http://bioinfo.uochb.cas.cz/rdf/sachem#chemical_entity> .
      ?chebi <http://bioinfo.uochb.cas.cz/rdf/sachem#has_same_skeleton> <https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=CHEBI:35516> .
    }
  }

  # Match the returned ChEBIs to Rhea undirected reactions.
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  ?chebi rdfs:label ?chebiName .
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve the set of metabolites involved in reactions catalyzed by human genes (HUMAN reference proteome)
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX rdfs:<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?reaction
  ?ecNumber
  ?protein
  ?ensemblTranscript
  ?ensemblGene
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .
    ?protein up:reviewed true .
    ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 .
    ?protein up:classifiedWith keywords:1185 .

    ?protein rdfs:seeAlso ?ensemblTranscript .
    ?ensemblTranscript a up:Transcript_Resource .
    ?ensemblTranscript up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/Ensembl> .
    ?ensemblTranscript up:transcribedFrom ?ensemblGene .

      {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
    UNION
      {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
    UNION
      {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
  }

  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi . # only considering small molecules participants
}
